In the template you can use HubL and display the right header, or the right navigation within a header (depending on how it's set up). Something like:

```{% if content.language.languageTag == 'de' %}
     {% global_partial path="../partials/header-de.html" %}
    {% else if content.language.languageTag == 'es' %}
     {% global_partial path="../partials/header-de.html" %}
    {% else %}
     {% global_partial path="../partials/header-en.html" %}
    {% endif %}```
That's how I'd approach it anyway so that they have one set of templates.

You could also have different templates with the different language headers and use the appropriate template for each language page.
